
[1]rebut

   REBUT', v.t. [See Butt and Pout.]

   To repel; to oppose by argument, plea or countervailing proof. [It is
   used by lawyers in a general sense.]

                                REBUT', v.i.

   1. To retire back. Obs.

   2. To answer, as a plaintiff's sur-rejoinder.

   The plaintiff may answer the rejoinder by a sur-rejoinder; on which the
   defendant may rebut.
